==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Natchez
<hw>Natch"ez</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld>
<def>A tribe of Indians who formerly lived near the site of the city of
<city>Natchez</city>, Mississippi. In 1729 they were subdued by the
French; the survivors joined the Creek Confederacy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Natchnee</ent>⟦br⟧
